A Teacher Invigilating The Ongoing KCSE Exam At Buna Boys School In Wajir County Is Nursing Serious Injuries After Being Stabbed By Students During An Exam. The Teacher Was Attacked After He Allegedly Confiscated Mobile Phones From Candidates During An Exam, An Act That Angered The Students. The Teacher Whose Name Has Not Been Released Was Attacked Severally On Friday Night Last Week. He Was Airlifted To Nairobi Today And Is Currently Admitted In Hospital. Police Have Launched Investigations Into The Incident.